subject: Fwd: US Congressmen send letter on Do Not Track to W3C
text:
---------- Forwarded message ----------
From: Noah Mendelsohn <nrm@arcanedomain.com>
Date: Wed, Jun 20, 2012 at 4:52 PM
Subject: US Congressmen send letter on Do Not Track to W3C
To: "www-tag@w3.org" <www-tag@w3.org>


US Congressmen Ed Markey and Joe Barton have sent a letter [1] on Do
Not Track to the W3C. (Forwarded [2] by Joseph Wender to the W3C
Public Tracking list).

Noah

[1] http://lists.w3.org/Archives/Public/public-tracking/2012Jun/att-0547/Letter_from_Rep_Markey_and_Barton_--_W3C_--_6-19-12.pdf
[2] http://lists.w3.org/Archives/Public/public-tracking/2012Jun/0547.html
